observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:

Strictly require the Collecting Officer to maintain a cashbook, record all transactions daily, close, rule, and certify the accounts and transactions in the cashbook at the end of each month. Moreover, remit daily all collections to the Municipal Treasurer;

Record all her collections daily in her cashbook including all amounts turned over to her by the Collecting Officer to reflect the correct balances of the collections, and deposit intact all collections made during the day.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Enjoin the Inventory Committee to conduct the one-time cleansing of all PPE accounts of the Municipality in accordance with the prescribed procedures embodied in COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence and condition;


Direct the designated Property Officer to maintain an updated property cards for each class of PPE;


Provide appropriate manpower for the efficient and effective execution of the property management of the municipality; and

Direct the Inventory Committee to prepare and submit a consolidated Report on the Physical Count of PPE (RPCPPE) and Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP); and journal entry vouchers drawn by the Accounting Unit for necessary adjusting entries as a result of disposal of properties.

We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:
Strictly require the Collecting Officer to maintain a cashbook, record all transactions daily, close, rule, and certify the accounts and transactions in the cashbook at the end of each month. Moreover, remit daily all collections to the Municipal Treasurer;


Record all her collections daily in her cashbook including all amounts turned over to her by the Collecting Officer to reflect the correct balances of the collections, and deposit intact all collections made during the day.
